    import cv2
    import numpy as np
    import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

    img_path = r"C:\water.jpg"
    img = cv2.imread(img_path)

    if img is None:
    raise FileNotFoundError("Image file not found. Check the path.")

    sampled_img = cv2.resize(img, (img.shape[1]//4, img.shape[0]//4), interpolation=cv2.INTER_AREA)

    def quantize(image, levels):
    bins = np.linspace(0, 256, levels+1)
    quantized = np.digitize(image, bins) - 1
    quantized_img = np.uint8((quantized / (levels - 1)) * 255)
    return quantized_img

    img_gray = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
    sampled_gray = cv2.resize(img_gray, (img_gray.shape[1]//4, img_gray.shape[0]//4), interpolation=cv2.INTER_AREA)

    quant_levels = [2, 4, 8, 16]

    quantized_grays = [quantize(img_gray, l) for l in quant_levels]
    quantized_colors = [quantize(img, l) for l in quant_levels]

    plt.figure(figsize=(16, 10))
    plt.subplot(3, len(quant_levels)+1, 1)
    plt.imshow(img_gray, cmap='gray')
    plt.title('Original Grayscale')
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(3, len(quant_levels)+1, 2)
    plt.imshow(sampled_gray, cmap='gray')
    plt.title('Sampled Grayscale')
    plt.axis('off')

    for i, q_img in enumerate(quantized_grays):
    plt.subplot(3, len(quant_levels)+1, i+3)
    plt.imshow(q_img, cmap='gray')
    plt.title(f'Quantized Gray\nLevels={quant_levels[i]}')
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(3, len(quant_levels)+1, len(quant_levels)+2)
    plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title('Original Color')
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(3, len(quant_levels)+1, len(quant_levels)+3)
    plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(sampled_img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title('Sampled Color')
    plt.axis('off')

    for i, q_img in enumerate(quantized_colors):
    plt.subplot(3, len(quant_levels)+1, len(quant_levels)+4+i)
    plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(q_img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(f'Quantized Color\nLevels={quant_levels[i]}')
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    print("Sampled grayscale image pixel values (center 5x5 block):")
    center = (sampled_gray.shape[0]//2, sampled_gray.shape[1]//2)
    print(sampled_gray[center[0]-2:center[0]+3, center[1]-2:center[1]+3])

    print("\nQuantized grayscale levels used in Levels=4:")
    print(np.unique(quantized_grays[1]))

    print("\nQuantized color levels used in Levels=4 (per channel approx):")
    unique_colors = np.unique(quantized_colors[1].reshape(-1, 3), axis=0)
    print(unique_colors)
